stick with 1.0.3 or try 1.0.11. I need to check for Maven availability, especially if there’s no internet connection, but since CI has internet, we can use a stable version. I'm curious about whether 1.0.11 requires Java 11, but JDK21 should be fine. Should we adjust our \\\"supported behavior public API\\\" test with Yasson present?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the test classpath to make Rest Assured’s JSON-B/Yasson classpath detection pass.\n\nChange made:\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added:\n    ```groovy\n    testImplementation 'org.eclipse:yasson:1.0.11'\n    ```\n\nReason:\n- Rest Assured only enables `ObjectMapperType.JSONB` when `org.eclipse.yasson.JsonBindingProvider` is present.\n- Adding only `javax.json.bind-api` provides the JSON-B interfaces for compilation, but not the Yasson provider class checked by `ObjectMapperResolver.isYassonInClassPath()`.\n\nI did not rerun the test command.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0513b7009d291482016a285148ea288196bb62679c99854360\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 740, "output": 1190, "cacheRead": 51200, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53130, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781027117603, "responseId": "resp_0513b7009d291482016a28512e59148196b72c33d09d0f1dd0"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating JSONB with Yasson**\n\nI’m thinking about projects using org.eclipse:yasson:1.0.3. The existing geronimo-json_1.1_spec works with older Yasson versions too. It seems like Rest-assured might default to Yasson as a factory. To avoid Java version issues, I wonder if we should stick with 1.0.3 or try 1.0.11. I need to check for Maven availability, especially if there’s no internet connection, but since CI has internet, we can use a stable version. I'm curious about whether 1.0.11 requires Java 11, but JDK21 should be fine. Should we adjust our \"supported behavior public API\" test with Yasson present?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0513b7009d291482016a28512fd30081968791cb33b46473e7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKFFIZLzSfz1DbhytOwAj53Tu69gEmzvP1N2BV_a7qh4GXJi1snKtVPYBEloZyXOKEmW3n_p-ac39jMyaPgYTqWKaFiROKEoeyhmKrM7Ksbvj2-m8kOqKDJUSxOOIkVeq4XpYBycOx-volHdO6nCW-ME06oxXtYVQvJhE8D42K4WQqPSVhSZPtyulsW0aTOGs35W1xpeZHV9iFMSeP4-BgK0UUYSMYpRql1faW7_CDIW5vyuf2AMZD2AZE9krluC4rH8p75rojF52XKLa7XsrOmgpsfBQhfVggmerJjnQWrXY0k3B3WXzvT7ZoYzKDnYr88Pq41YCiRKY_zoO9fPaqFxeW5lLzwUTUu8nEl0HePVqr8Ux0LblQrd0jOu-7ksdsSq_Wnp9AUCG2qAbAoaep4y6ZH4I9Ujoo_ivgUZaG3MuuDC_FzV9J8h-sIC_pjsogEv4BJJvFtR2nEq2hT_z7VuXV0huDxboyf8HODjB_Cq4XEivfpY0f0241dns-FX_3olSgW6ch7aJHJqrfeJrrGePohBco8v3iLys2rnNysvNmVVLe_subKyrZ39abQns8eaK8CVdCR9hBAFjD6W8MfynThNWZSrRcERoq33I8P1DlvmNTgss83sxD8dGa1iCyoBsrWVLdwtEDyO0x3riX-vwIPKmKzTJOlI4U-2qf7eYJaAOjOVd-3u6X4_J40jNXxE_2kqs50h5Ype184R2ileQcfde56YUqX0CMe6jAm5oL5SH6sLYBbFJBIaJ6GGpbkCHAmZ1o_upty7BGN5TUf4RoJw3D3ZWm1g0Hm6cRDE0ZAHDBOBnnpLqd9gz5n0SeEE4fQsXMwWb8EToN2vNNWSXClGmcMPA3yPnVxzscBZSzteCmNWjDotqB2J-rsnfKpOBEsNXBinPNqHLLfkuV6sxn8X4YXk_rQcVfP0UzEtVDkjfwoOqR3lDm2HPLbtWxkmxpRLCbwqJm1uYL6CElRNwDH7xKaNLiD232hmZ6Gp5buxNL7XaTikdnFqLM2oPlEH3oWUYaL7eQP1O8-FqJFyFpKFxkoX6VsJ4gURy3OekofnGUorZUfMuedcKnlvkPKoJrz1yO02ZXjzKTCbor7s9x_