ck with 1.0.3 or try 1.0.11. I need to check for Maven availability, especially if there’s no internet connection, but since CI has internet, we can use a stable version. I'm curious about whether 1.0.11 requires Java 11, but JDK21 should be fine. Should we adjust our \\\"supported behavior public API\\\" test with Yasson present?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the test classpath to make Rest Assured’s JSON-B/Yasson classpath detection pass.\n\nChange made:\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added:\n    ```groovy\n    testImplementation 'org.eclipse:yasson:1.0.11'\n    ```\n\nReason:\n- Rest Assured only enables `ObjectMapperType.JSONB` when `org.eclipse.yasson.JsonBindingProvider` is present.\n- Adding only `javax.json.bind-api` provides the JSON-B interfaces for compilation, but not the Yasson provider class checked by `ObjectMapperResolver.isYassonInClassPath()`.\n\nI did not rerun the test command.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0513b7009d291482016a285148ea288196bb62679c99854360\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 740, "output": 1190, "cacheRead": 51200, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53130, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781027117603, "responseId": "resp_0513b7009d291482016a28512e59148196b72c33d09d0f1dd0"}, "toolResults": []}
