[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Class.forName usage**\n\nI'm considering using Class.forName with the argument \"java.lang.String\" instead of JsonbMapper.class.getName(). It seems that this might work better because it utilizes a JDK class that's available without requiring metadata in native. If RestAssured.class.getName() might cause issues, perhaps using String.class could be a better approach. I wonder if Class.forName on application library classes really does need metadata, and it looks like it might. This might be key to passing tests and avoiding NoClassDef errors.\n\n**Addressing coverage issues**\n\nI’m noticing there's a report suggesting that there could be no coverage after an agent run, which worries me. Changing the focus to String seems like a solid plan. Additionally, I've realized that using MethodHandles might pose access issues since they’re non-public. The user mentioned that there are many generated tests invoking these calls, which could be a problem. I also need to look into the JSONB tests that are failing—something about the metadata might be causing serialization errors. Let's dig into those error results!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0513b7009d291482016a285234ad8881969226bf413c57271f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKFJPGFsrw4obyQ3iSWx7jsBchfPC2f6H7pNtRZzkrj7Pq-vHF08gas13aFbqJQ3J4HPInCFDzWlgiLPrBOFEcxjls9UCXb_u75h-lawVsTGnI02Kod2198vce2OTBT__Uui2UVknZGjwmrOhxUSC1Ehj14R_ArAAxMzNLySuIVFQvev54A1lfNVdlWvlYYFYdNKVnJ5Aedg4if2eJUycy4FzPows3Jg_9a2yoMzbMvr0HU0rpzTQ_G4oDXKG-o9gXwKIxoBpyhAxdbKEJCdjWIYrIngOphaq08yNOOtIhXARMZBnFglbdenk83FxqPd1HU0mRABk2_QD-N66lqzxnmGX450-If85rzlu7IDbqkcYwM8c3yy24a8d9JrQ7pFJfmnbESXV7MF3lCWvNV0ECMnrRqOR_1gRNCk0f10TMwoq61cl8PWdZsr37obC6SFKgOcPCo22o_o7sEbsyrdJnzuaOfMr7rsu_QC991t3-ttMmaKOWOifzlNaf-iPzFOQvCzViUxrKvR7PvuO6T5Qm0lNmswGQWdvZTl5kfMH25hGvN9D4qyX4dA8_O6bky4lhLrNv3F61KY9ysuYABz1ZV6fx